            <Title>Question 12</Title>
            <Synopsis>Do current federal programs encourage and support domestic collaboration?</Synopsis>
            <Text>Do current federal programs encourage and support domestic collaboration?

Answer:

The cancelling of the MRS programme has had a notable impact on national-level facilities. Indeed, we have observed a policy movement toward only fundamental international facilities (admittedly with some exceptions).Nonetheless, researchers are especially cognizant that the view a facility is “National level” is now a derogatory term in the eyes of many at the funding councils.
</Text>
